FT  12 SEP 94 / Arts (Openings): Lyric Theatre, London
Neil Bartlett, known for his theatrical use of camp and portrayals of gay
sexuality, launches his new regime as artistic director of the Lyric
Theatre, Hammersmith with a new staging of The Portrait of Dorian Grey. The
cast includes Maria Aitken and the travesty performer Bette Bourne.
